<section id="content.type.image-gallery">
    <title>The Image Gallery Content Type</title>

    <para>
        The Image Gallery content type provides a simple way to display a grid of clickable
        thumbnails in &product.longname;. Images can be added to the gallery via drag-and-drop (for
        a <link linkend="content.add.dnd.supported-browsers">supported web browser</link>), or
        selected from any previously added Image content entries. Clicking on an image shows a
        larger or full-size version in a "lightbox" presentation.
    </para>

    <section>
        <title>Creating an Image Gallery</title>

        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                Please refer to <xref linkend="content.add"/> to see the process for choosing a
                content type. Choose the Image Gallery content type. The new Image Gallery is
                displayed:

                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="images/screen-image_gallery-start.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>

                <note>
                    <title>Drop Files Here &mdash; the <emphasis>gallery</emphasis> area</title>

                    <para>
                        For browsers that <link linkend="content.add.dnd.supported-browsers">support
                        drag-and-drop file operations</link>, the area where images appear is
                        labelled "Images (drop files here)"; otherwise the label is "Images".
                    </para>
                </note>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
                Choose an approach for adding images:

                <orderedlist numeration="upperalpha">
                    <listitem>
                        <emphasis role="bold">Using Drag-and-Drop</emphasis>

                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Note: this only works with a
                            <link linkend="content.add.dnd.supported-browsers">supported web
                            browser</link>.</emphasis>
                        </para>

                        <orderedlist numeration="arabic">
                            <listitem>
                                Drag one or more images from outside your browser onto the
                                <emphasis>gallery</emphasis> area. An upload dialog appears:

                                <mediaobject>
                                    <imageobject>
                                        <imagedata fileref="images/dialog-upload_content.png"/>
                                    </imageobject>
                                </mediaobject>
                            </listitem>

                            <listitem>
                                Click <guibutton>Upload</guibutton> to upload the images. A progress
                                dialog is displayed while the images are uploaded:

                                <mediaobject>
                                    <imageobject>
                                        <imagedata fileref="images/dialog-upload_content-progress.png"/>
                                    </imageobject>
                                </mediaobject>

                                When the upload completes, thumbnails of the images are displayed:

                                <mediaobject>
                                    <imageobject>
                                        <imagedata fileref="images/screen-image_gallery-uploaded.png"/>
                                    </imageobject>
                                </mediaobject>
                            </listitem>
                        </orderedlist>
                    </listitem>

                    <listitem>
                        <emphasis role="bold">By Selecting Content</emphasis>

                        <orderedlist numeration="arabic">
                            <listitem>
                                Click the <emphasis>gallery</emphasis> area. A tooltip dialog
                                appears:

                                <mediaobject>
                                    <imageobject>
                                        <imagedata fileref="images/dialog-image_gallery-tooltip-new.png"/>
                                    </imageobject>
                                </mediaobject>
                            </listitem>

                            <listitem>
                                Click <guibutton>Browse</guibutton>. A content selection dialog appears:

                                <mediaobject>
                                    <imageobject>
                                        <imagedata fileref="images/dialog-image_gallery-select.png"/>
                                    </imageobject>
                                </mediaobject>
                            </listitem>

                            <listitem>
                                Select one or more images. Click <guibutton>Select</guibutton>. The
                                tooltip dialog is updated with your selection:

                                <mediaobject>
                                    <imageobject>
                                        <imagedata fileref="images/dialog-image_gallery-tooltip-selected.png"/>
                                    </imageobject>
                                </mediaobject>
                            </listitem>

                            <listitem>
                                Click off the <emphasis>gallery</emphasis> area. Thumbnails of the
                                images are displayed:

                                <mediaobject>
                                    <imageobject>
                                        <imagedata fileref="images/screen-image_gallery-uploaded.png"/>
                                    </imageobject>
                                </mediaobject>
                            </listitem>
                        </orderedlist>
                    </listitem>
                </orderedlist>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
                Complete any other changes, then click <guibutton>Save</guibutton>.
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>

    <section>
        <title>Using an Image Gallery</title>

        <para>
            After the content entry is saved, clicking on an image thumbnail causes a "lightbox"
            presentation of the image &mdash; a dark page overlay reduces attention on the page
            while viewing images.

            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="images/screen-image_gallery-lightbox.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>

            While the lightbox presentation is active, hovering the mouse over the left or right
            side of the image displays an arrow if, respectively, there are previous or next images
            available. Clicking on the image when the arrow is visible presents the previous or next
            image.
        </para>

        <para>
            Click the <guibutton>X</guibutton> at the top right of the image, or anywhere off the
            image, to exit the lightbox presentation.
        </para>

        <note>
            <title>Using the Tableau theme?</title>

            <para>
                Please review <link linkend="tableau.image-gallery">the adjustments to image
                galleries</link> when the Tableau theme is active.
            </para>
        </note>
    </section>

    <section>
        <title>Removing Images from the Gallery</title>

        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                Click <guibutton>Edit</guibutton> in the &product.longname; toolbar to begin
                editing.

                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="images/toolbar-content-edit.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
                Click the <emphasis>gallery</emphasis> area containing thumbnails. A tooltip dialog
                listing all the images in the gallery appears:

                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="images/dialog-image_gallery-tooltip-selected.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
                Click <guibutton>Clear</guibutton> beside an image you wish to remove. The image is
                removed from the list of thumbnails in the tooltip dialog, and its thumbnail is
                removed from the <emphasis>gallery</emphasis> area.
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
                Click <guibutton>Save</guibutton> to complete the removal of the image(s).
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
</section>
